OL,3,CD-Day veteran's great grandson born
OL,4,Cduring 80th anniversary commemorations
OL,6,F"I was thrilled to receive the news of
OL,7,Fmy great grandson who was born as the
OL,8,Fferry was making its way to Normandy
OL,9,Fon Tuesday ` same day as my father's
OL,10,Fbirthday," he said.
OL,12,F"He was due to arrive on D-Day, June
OL,13,F6, but couldn't wait. I'm so pleased
OL,14,Fhe arrived in time for the
OL,15,Fcelebrations."
OL,17,FMr Morgan, from Crewe, was a code-
OL,18,Fbreaker who landed on Gold Beach in
OL,19,Fthe early evening of D-Day and saw the
OL,20,Fgrim sight of drowned servicemen.
