OL,3,CD-Day veteran's great grandson born
OL,4,Cduring 80th anniversary commemorations
OL,6,F"Every time I went on duty, I had the
OL,7,Fsame wireless operators with me and I
OL,8,Flost all three," he said. "One was
OL,9,Fkilled by friendly fire, the other two
OL,10,FI've just found side-by-side in the
OL,11,Fcemetery at Ryes Cemetery.
OL,13,F"They were in a Forward Direction Post
OL,14,Fwhen the Germans dropped teller mines
OL,15,Fon them and killed the pair of them.
OL,16,FI'm so lucky it wasn't me. I think of
OL,17,Fthose lads very often."
